  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.35.8",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 35,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Thy wickedness {may hurt} a man as thou {art}; and thy righteousness {may profit} the son of man.",
    "hash": "95c35712677acd2b6be78c7374bbb250e2b73af185e5c67f021dcd6448e3edcb"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.35.9",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 35,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "By reason of the multitude of oppressions they make {the oppressed} to cry: they cry out by reason of the arm of the mighty.",
    "hash": "d834ffcf8c68b4e8f170469ad89812edf56bb4b2a6dba7e95c7df65413f9f191"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.35.10",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 35,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "But none saith, Where {is} God my maker, who giveth songs in the night;",
    "hash": "098fc60e7458b700d860cdb8e54ca0bd429bcaa6ee617810ff62645480ff33bf"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.35.11",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 35,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Who teacheth us more than the beasts of the earth, and maketh us wiser than the fowls of heaven?",
    "hash": "d6a74cc5573f2a573920f1366a7f9a1cc10c50f7bdfd3d8e76b1cfc743acd77a"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.35.12",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 35,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "There they cry, but none giveth answer, because of the pride of evil men.",
    "hash": "f657c26659a535168cf59709dab096a0c74c0c339a487627cdc3d92e6de33982"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.35.13",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 35,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Surely God will not hear vanity, neither will the Almighty regard it.",
    "hash": "c39b05fe64570fb14f1af48faf6689345f6f0fb43ef4760e0bff59c4ed58def6"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.35.14",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 35,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Although thou sayest thou shalt not see him, {yet} judgment {is} before him; therefore trust thou in him.",
    "hash": "fc940b2dac23d96d4c760eb937372c90cfbcfa437645eb34a480fcb1a6448ca8"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.35.15",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 35,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "But now, because {it is} not {so}, he hath visited in his anger; yet he knoweth {it} not in great extremity: {he hath: that is, God hath} {he knoweth: that is, Job knoweth}",
    "hash": "d9e942cfeae009cb017d748004b1dc02c5cf1964534788b9ff8fa274f9fe479e"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.35.16",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 35,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Therefore doth Job open his mouth in vain; he multiplieth words without knowledge.",
    "hash": "f19d4cb5f514c43f29ba13bdbc94116f403863b2f83c6347c72b1cbb6ab9e3c1"
  }
]